    "summary": "I am the founder and managing partner of SenseGuide. SenseGuide supports NGO's, public and corporate organizations with human centered sensemaking. We deliver insights and meaning build on the reality of day-to-day narratives. \n\nOur approach has its roots in complex adaptive systems theory, naturalistic sensemaking and cognitive sciences. It consist of capturing large volumes of micro-narratives from daily life, powerful datavisualisations and analytics, system mapping and robust sensemaking methods.  The goal is to minimize cognitive bias, identify patterns and weak signals early and utilize the rich context of narratives to inform strategy, impact monitoring, accountability, evaluation and learning.\n\nSome of the projects I have worked on are: \n- the Work: No Child's Business program in India, Ivory Coast, Jordan, Mali, Uganda and Vietnam with Hivos, Save the Children and Unicef\n- improving food security and preventing malnutrition in Bangladesh (PROOFS program) with BoPinc\n- development of the Flourishing Community Index with Cordaid (monitoring of fragile communities in a.o Burundi, DR Congo - awarded by the UK Evaluation Society)\n- monitoring & evaluation programs in a.o Uganda, Niger, Tanzania (World Bank), Mozambique, Benin\n- civic engagement of potential reforms in Saudi Arabia (Vision 2030)\n- impact monitoring of local government policy in social domain (a.o. Almere, Amsterdam, Apeldoorn, Assen, Ermelo, Harderwijk, Purmerend, Rotterdam, Tilburg, Veenendaal, Zaanstad, Zeewolde)\n- assessment of the VOG policy (letter of good conduct) for Dutch Ministry of Security and Justice\n- monitoring and enabling learning and development: a.o. cases with ING, Dutch Ministry of Defense, Mondriaan GGZ, \n- monitoring and learning of national programs in health and wellbeing (Waardigheid en trots op Locatie, Anders Werken Zorg en Welzijn)\n- understanding consumer behaviour for sustainable water management\n- explorative research to mentality change in metropolitan car use with Greenpeace Mindworks",
